							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have been struggling with this question as well.  I do realize that this thread is a little old and so that some of the information may be outdated.  However, I do have some related questions that I would like to ask in order to clarify some things for myself.
<br />

<br />
1.)  Dirges get a fear effect.  This makes the targetted mob run away, but is there a limited distance that it runs away and then comes back?  If not then I can just envision someone doing this at the wrong time and then the group chasing said mob all the way across Norrath.
<br />

<br />
2.)  The classic lifetap vs. power tap issue.  I noticed that Dirges do get two abilities that drain power over time (Thuri's Doleful Thrust at lvl 29 and Bereavement [Thuri's upgrade i belive] later on).  Is the power damage that these do negligable or is it simply a matter of Troubs doing it better?
<br />

<br />
3.)  Lastly I noticed that several Dirge abilities lowered "Trauma" mitigation.  What exactly is this?  When I look at my character's stats I do not see Trauma but I do see disease.  Have they changed the name of this resist and thus does this debuff alow our disease attacks to be more effective?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
