						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1.) They run away for about the same amount of time that Mez holds.... basically it's mez.... tell your party not to chase the mobs... mobs do not run in EQ2 they die in the heat of battle every time.... if you are chasing after a running mob... you are confused about which version of EQ you are playing...  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
2.) Powertap makes Troubs very desired on raids... however it makes them less desireable solo or in groups... basically 1 troub can drain all the power of a caster mob solo... but to do it you take a major hit to DPS... and it's power will be gone when the mob is at like 25% HP.  Dirges having HP taps keeps them alive longer when solo and in groups with low heal power... plus adds DPS.  Since a large chunk of a mobs DPS is it's power pool on a raid that is your primary job.... besides troubs the only other big power drainers are enchanters.
<br />

<br />
3.) Trauma mitigation... priests have a cure that removes trauma effects... I have NO IDEA what is classified as Trauma.
<br />

<br />
Plus you forgot one...
<br />

<br />
4.) Dirges get Rez... which is handy at times... although priests can give you a rez rock also.  Troubs get HP Regen... HP regen is useless... it takes 2/5 of your concentration and over the course of the battle you might get enough HP to take 1/10 of a hit from the mob... no troub ever uses this spell... not even when solo.  Even if hey cut the concentration required from 2 to 1 would any of us use it... it's just that useless.
<br />

<br />
and one other thing...
<br />

<br />
5.) Dirges get JMoA it's a class training... it's massive amounts of runspeed... faster than any horse I believe.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thedauntless.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://tinyurl.com/6qjqw/blah.png" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
