							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Aye fear is on a 20 sec timer it makes the mob run for 20 secs then when it breaks they come back for you. It is not a GREAT spell but not BAD either. Not as nice as mez because in dungeons mobs can sometimes get stuck in walls. Which will lock your whole grp in an encounter. This is a very emergency use only spell, Troubs defintly have the advantage here. 
<br />

<br />
Dirges get 2 lifetaps which can help some..but are not neccesarily amazing i most of the time do not use the DD "Cry of the Dead" because it is not that much dmg or of a life tap this is only really used when you REALLY need hps and a healer is down or you have none. We can drain some power at lvl 50 I believe i take off about 200pnts with berevment every 10secs. So it aint bad but prolly about 1/3 of what a troub could do. 
<br />

<br />
Trauma mitigation debuff = Melee mitigation debuff.......it reduces enemies ac allowing all slash/pierce/crush dmg to hit harder VERY nice spell.
<br />

<br />
Dirges late game and in raids are GREAT for rez....we hands down get best rez in game.....15sec recast in combat rez...that brings peeps back at 44% helath and power. No other class comes close in this(providing we dont get nerfed which i have a feeling we will) I have singlehandly had raids where i rezed 1/2 of the raid.
