							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Oh yeah good point on fear making mobs bugged... hopefully they will  fix that... but it's an issue I forgot.  If they fix it I think you will have the advantage... because when I mez the mob stays there and people might mistarget it... yours moves away reducing the risk of a mistarget....
<br />

<br />
The other advantage of dirge rez is that dirges get sneak and evac... priests do not (ok 1 priest gets evac and one gets sneak... but that's outta 6 priests).... so a dirge can sneak all the way to the corpse... rez it and if he gets aggro... evac.  And yes we usually have a dirge on rez duty if needed on a rough raid... because if people are dying it's obvious the priests are too busy to rez...
<br />

<br />
I have 6 power taps.... 3 of them good ones.
<br />

<br />
- strong - 
<br />
Straight power tap
<br />
Flanking DPS + power tap
<br />
DPS + power tap
<br />
- weaker -
<br />
AC debuff + power tap
<br />
Snare + power tap
<br />
Arrow + power tap
<br />

<br />
In ANY battle I use the flanking, dps, and ac debuff power taps.... or really I should say depletions... because we use more power than we gain back... taps isn't truly what they are.... even if you take the best return vs cost one if you cast it 4 times odds are 1 will be a resist and you will have spent power.
<br />

<br />
So in a typical fight... I drain alot of power without trying.... but as long as the mob has 10% power he has been able to cast spells the whole time... so draining ALOT is not good enough you have to drain it ALL... and prior enough to the mobs death so that it has had an impact on the battle... more so then just adding HP-based DPS and killing it faster.
<br />

<br />
The best mobs to drain are priests... because they have higher mitigation + power = HP for them.... so getting the mob to 10% HP and 100% power = mob can go back to 100% HP and 75% power.... the fact you lose DPS to drain more matters little because a drain to the power pool has a larger impact on the mobs "implied" HP pool.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.thedauntless.org" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://tinyurl.com/6qjqw/blah.png" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
