							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Cry of the Dead is useless IMO unless you need life for yourself for the mere fact that if you look at it it does  about 200dmg and taps 100 life which no isnt bad BUT is a 3sec cast which is TOO long for the dmg and you also cannot move while casting it, and also can be interuppted. For these resons it is useless unless you need life.....at lvl 50 my melee attacks during those 3 secs will do closer to 300-400 dmg during that time. Unless our DD's dmg are increased as a dirge they are ussually more of a hinderance on your DPS then they are a help. But if you dont believe me do the parses.....b/c of the casting time they actually do less dmg then regular melee attacks. Same thing with our grp aoe dd...this is even worse however because it stuns YOU for 1sec after it hits. 
<br />

<br />
Only use for the dd's IMO(in a group that is) is to get into range for bow shot.  For example i will use all my melee skills on a target que up my Main DD(NOT CoD, the one that hits for 400-500) and while it is casting move into bow range while queing my bow CA.....then que lanets while runing back in melee range. This way there is no time time lost i am casting a spell while going in and out of range. Other then that i believe all our DDs are useless with good weapons you do more dmg on auto attack at least according to all my parses. 
